{"action": "edit", "code": "def get_second_most_common_color(input_grid: np.ndarray) -> int:\n    \"\"\"\n    Given an input grid, returns the color with the second most pixels.\n\n    Args:\n    input_grid: A numpy array representing the input grid.\n\n    Returns:\n    An integer representing the color with the second most pixels.\n    \"\"\"\n    unique, counts = np.unique(input_grid, return_counts=True)\n    sorted_counts = np.argsort(-counts)\n    return unique[sorted_counts[1]]\ndef main(input_grid: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    c1 = get_second_most_common_color(input_grid)\n    c2 = get_third_most_common_color(input_grid)\n    for i in range(4):\n        input_grid = find_largest_matrix_with_c1_c2_pixels(input_grid, c1, c2)\n    return input_grid\ndef find_largest_matrix_with_c1_c2_pixels(input_grid: np.ndarray, c1: int, c2: int) -> np.ndarray:\n    \"\"\"\n    Find the largest matrix with only c1 and c2 pixels in color, and at least one pixel with color c2 on each boundary.\n    Replace pixels of color c1 with yellow.\n\n    Args:\n    input_grid: A numpy array representing the input grid.\n    c1: An integer representing the color to be replaced with yellow.\n    c2: An integer representing the color to be kept in the matrix.\n\n    Returns:\n    A numpy array representing the modified input grid.\n    \"\"\"\n    labeled_array, num_features = label(input_grid == c2)\n    largest_component = 0\n    largest_component_size = 0\n    for i in range(1, num_features + 1):\n        component_size = np.sum(labeled_array == i)\n        if component_size > largest_component_size:\n            largest_component = i\n            largest_component_size = component_size\n    top_boundary = np.min(np.where(labeled_array == largest_component)[0])\n    bottom_boundary = np.max(np.where(labeled_array == largest_component)[0])\n    left_boundary = np.min(np.where(labeled_array == largest_component)[1])\n    right_boundary = np.max(np.where(labeled_array == largest_component